      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine and a 6-speed manual transmission. This specimen has been maintained with technical rigor, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and a recent valve clearance adjustment to maintain optimal timing and compression. The chassis has been addressed with rear subframe reinforcement, mitigating a known platform weakness and ensuring structural rigidity under high lateral loads. Performance is anchored by a factory M-Variable differential lock and a precision-tuned suspension featuring upgraded polyurethane bushings. While the bodywork shows honest signs of use, the mechanical drivetrain remains tight, offering the visceral feedback and analog throttle response that defines this generation of M-cars.",
